
<section id="ControlTimeread">
  <title>Time Reading</title>

  <para>
    Opcodes one can use to read time values are:
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem><para><link linkend="readclock"><citetitle>readclock</citetitle></link></para></listitem>
      <listitem><para><link linkend="rtclock"><citetitle>rtclock</citetitle></link></para></listitem>
      <listitem><para><link linkend="timeinstk"><citetitle>timeinstk</citetitle></link></para></listitem>
      <listitem><para><link linkend="timeinsts"><citetitle>timeinsts</citetitle></link></para></listitem>
      <listitem><para><link linkend="times"><citetitle>times</citetitle></link></para></listitem>
      <listitem><para><link linkend="timek"><citetitle>timek</citetitle></link></para></listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </para>
  <para>
    You can obtain the system date using:
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem><para><link linkend="date"><citetitle>date</citetitle></link> - Returns the number seconds since 1 January 1970.</para></listitem>
      <listitem><para><link linkend="dates"><citetitle>dates</citetitle></link> - Returns as a string the date and time specified.</para></listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </para>
  <para>
    You can also set up counters using <link linkend="clockoff"><citetitle>clockoff</citetitle></link> and <link linkend="clockon"><citetitle>clockon</citetitle></link>.
  </para>
</section>
